nce >= 0.8\n\nOutput your evaluation as JSON matching the NetworkEvaluation schema.\n", "user_message": "Evaluate this synthesis network:\n\nTARGET MOLECULE: Serine\nOVERALL STRATEGY: This network centers serine synthesis on the strongest literature-supported prebiotic routes: Strecker and phosphoro-Strecker chemistry from glycolaldehyde, followed by nitrile hydrolysis to serine, while embedding those steps in a connected cross-environment network. Hydrothermal reactions generate reduced C1-C3 feedstocks (formate, formaldehyde, pyruvate) on Fe-S and Fe-oxide minerals under vent conditions. Surface environments convert formaldehyde into glycolaldehyde and glycolonitrile and then into serine nitrile or N-phosphoro-serine nitrile under cyanide-rich, phosphate-buffered, UV-exposed, wet-dry conditions on borate, sulfide, TiO2, montmorillonite, and phosphate minerals. Biochemical/prebiotic steps perform hydrolysis and mild nonenzymatic transamination analogs to connect hydrothermal alpha-keto chemistry with surface cyanide chemistry. Ten distinct pathways are enumerated, but all respect the literature emphasis that direct Strecker/phosphoro-Strecker routes are the most established, whereas alpha-keto links are more speculative evolutionary bridges.\n\nMOLECULES (18 nodes):\n  - mol_001: CO2 (carbon dioxide) [starting]\n  - mol_002: H2 (hydrogen) [starting]\n  - mol_003: NH3 (ammonia) [starting]\n  - mol_004: HCN (hydrogen cyanide) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_005: CH2O2 (formic acid/formate) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_006: CH2O (formaldehyde) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_007: C2H4O2 (glycolaldehyde) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_008: C2H3NO (glyoxylic acid/glyoxylate) [intermediate]\n  - mol_009: C2H3NO (glycolonitrile) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_010: C3H4N2O (serine nitrile) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_011: C3H9N3O4P (N-phosphoro-serine nitrile) [intermediate]\n  - mol_012: C3H7NO3 (serine) [target]\n  - mol_013: C3H4O3 (pyruvic acid/pyruvate) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_0